@node demo2 "About the demo"


    This demo represents only a very little part of the complete game, by the
way, it is very limited, here is a list of the features of the demo:


* only 3 places available
* the intro anim is not complete
* the demo is only in french and english
* the voices are only available in "Français" mode


In this demo, your only aim is to find a secret way (find where it is :-))

The voices of the demo are not the ones in the complete game, they were recorded
quickly for the demo so do not care about the little bugs of some sounds.

The demo runs perfectly but sometime, there is a little bug only present in the
demo.
When you want to run a software after the demo, it may crash so we recommend
you to rebbot after using the demo.

@endnode


@node hard2 "Hardware required"


    The demo runs on any AGA Amiga with at least a 68020 (A1200/A4000) and
4 Mb of FAST RAM.

Of course, the better the Amiga is, the better the demo will run.

The demo supports every Motorola's processor since the 68020 (020, 030, 040, 060)

The more powerful the processor is, the faster the transitions would be :-)




                    @{b}WHAT ARE YOU WAITING TO UPGRADE ???@{ub}

@endnode


@node instal2 "Installation..."



    To install the demo, you'll need 10 Mb of drive space.

There is no Installer script because there is no special tricks to do (no
assigns, nothing to copy to C or Libs...)
You just need to copy the Nothingness_DEMO DRAWER where you want.


@endnode


@node usage2 "Getting started..."


    As you would see, you are in front of a main panel as in Monkey Island, you
would find all the necessary commands to move, to act or to look around you.
When the mouse pointer changes, you can click on the right mouse button to
execute the action (if it's an eye, the action is "Look at ...").

In the intro page, you can set the language.

In the options, you can save the game, quit it or replaying where you are..


                                ENJOY THE GAME ;-)

@endnode


