It is enough tosay this and that's all but the actual situation of the Amiga
makes me wanting to say more.

The Amiga seems to die and it's a pity, I guests those who love the Amiga
to make them known, to buy the magazins that are talking about the Amiga,
to upgrade their computer, to contact us, to write to VisCorp, QuickPack,
PhaseV, TEAM 17 or the others...

The Amiga can survive only if SHE has your supports.
One thing is sure, Melina Softworks and Cassiope Development will never stop
developping on this computer because we are passionated.
For us, it is better to disappear than stop.

The new Amiga's boss must hear the users, when he will be known, we would
contact him to purpose him our ideas for new Amigas and for helping them to
develop the futur Amigas. (if he is ok, of course).


As you can see, nothing is lost, new groups are appearing everywhere in the
world and the futur is not dead anymore if you decide tou change your
